description.narrative: UNICEF led the implementation of a national micronutrient survey that will update key nutrition data and examine factors underlying persistently poor nutrition indicators. In partnership with MOH, UNICEF is implementing the migration of nutrition reporting from the current online ONA reporting system to DHIS2, integrating nutrition reporting into government health information systems including the plan to support capacity strengthening of government for increased programme ownership. The maternal nutrition survey that is underway will feed into C4D campaigns and interventions targeting women of childbearing age. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:14/01/2020
